review_data: Reviewed in the United States on June 29, 2021
name: AmazonCustomer
title: My All-Time Favorite Skyr (kind of like yogurt)
review: The Peach Cloudberry flavor skyr tastes like heaven on earth. I have achalasia, and getting food down can be difficult. This works fine. Other flavors are too acidic, but the peach cloudberry is both delicious and doesn't hurt/burn my esophagus. I've recommended this to fellow achalasia sufferers. Whether or not you have achalasia, this is the BEST SKYR! Highly recommend.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on April 29, 2021
name: JM
title: Creamy but flavorless
review: I eat various forms of yogurt morning, noon, and night. This has a bit more creaminess that 0% fat greek yogurt, which makes it feel more luxurious, and I think the tiny bit of fat (2 g) balances out the tartness that low fat yogurt often has, but I can only taste the tiniest amount of peach, and I can only assume a cloudberry is some sort of berry mist that floats above my spoon. It's non-existent in this yogurt.There are tons of better tasting yogurts out there, with better macros, that cost much less.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on August 14, 2018
name: Saurabh Kothari
title: Dangerous for consumption
review: This yoghurt gets spoiled very easily. I have about 5 different types of yogurt in my fridge and this is the only one which develops fungus as early as 3 days after the best before date. Fungus can be dangerous for consumption. I contacted the company a week ago and they are yet to respond. Not only disappointing, but dangerous.
